cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) category as it deals with object localization in images. It also involves the use of deep reinforcement learning, which suggests it could also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) categories. The use of bounding boxes and transformation actions suggests it could also belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) category. Finally, the use of reinforcement learning for training the model suggests it could also belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) category.
